<TITLE> Army starts Aila relief ops </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 26 (bdnews24.com)Army has started relief operation at 12 Aila-affected Upazilas in four districts, an ISPR press release said on Tuesday. The affected Upazilas are Nildumur, Ashashuni, Shyamnagar in Satkhira, Mirzaganaj, Baufal, Kalapara, Golachipa and Sadar Upazila in Patuakhali, Dumuria and Paikgachha in Khulna, Morelganj and Sharankhola in Bagerhat. Army members are there in aid of civil administration. They are distributing rice, lentil, flattened rice, molasses, biscuits, salt, drinking water, water purification tablets, oral saline, matches, candle lights among the people. Sufficient number of tents have also been kept stand by to help the cyclone-affected people. Four medical teams are providing treatments to them. A mobile hospital has also been kept stand by. Four high-powered water purification treatment plants have been installed to ease drinking water crisis. Twenty vessels are also carrying out rescue activities. bd
